    "text": "Ramp back, but gently — your recovery signals are ahead of your tissues. Today's 76% recovery is comfortably above your 7-day average of 69%, and your HRV of 63 ms is back over its 30-day baseline of 61.8 ms, so the illness looks behind you. But your acute-to-chronic load ratio is 0.62 — a week of missed training means you're temporarily detrained relative to a month ago, and jumping straight to full volume is where comeback injuries happen. This week: two easy runs and one moderate one, no intensity, roughly two-thirds of a normal week. If that lands well, resume the normal October build next week — the plan bends, the goal doesn't.",
